# ── Build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The static binary built by `make build` lands at the repo root.
/airom
/airom.exe
# goreleaser output (release builds, archives, checksums, SBOM/AIBOM attachments).
/dist/
# Scratch space for local experiments.
/tmp/

# ── Test & coverage artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.test
*.out
coverage.out
coverage.html
# Never ignore checked-in fixtures or goldens, whatever their extension —
# testdata trees reproduce real-world files byte-for-byte (see §14).
!**/testdata/**

# ── Fuzzing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Go's interesting-input fuzz cache lives in $GOCACHE/fuzz, OUTSIDE the repo,
# so there is nothing to ignore here. Checked-in seed corpora and minimized
# failing inputs under **/testdata/fuzz/ are deliberately TRACKED (every binary
# header parser is fuzzed in CI, §13/§14) — do NOT add testdata/fuzz to this
# file.

# ── Go workspace files ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# go.work is a local, per-developer multi-module setup; never commit it.
go.work
go.work.sum

# ── Editors & IDEs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/*
# Shared, non-personal editor config is allowed back in:
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# ── OS noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store

# ── Documentation site (Mintlify) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# `mint dev` local preview cache/build output; the .mdx sources ARE tracked.
/docs-site/.mintlify/
/docs-site/node_modules/
